<plot>This Sports Parade short's theme is participant-sports all across the USA or, at least, west of the Mississippi Rivers. Skiing in Aspen, Colorado (when it was still a real town) and amateur-rodeo in New Mexico. The came visits Abilene, Kansas, where greyhound-racing with the dogs chasing live rabbits is a pastime and then wanders over to Phoenix, Arizona for a look at hot-rodders racing their modified jalopies, before automobile companies and NASCAR took over the world.</plot><url>http://localhost:8983/solr/movie.html?647576</url></doc>
